    "THE MIAMI TIMES MIAMI FLORIDA PAGE FOUR a n FLORIDAS FAVORITE COLORED WEEKLY Entered as Second Claes Matter August 9 1927 at the Post Office at Miami Florida under the act of March S 1876 Published every Saturday by the Magic Printery office at 1112 NW Third Avenue Miami Florida Telephone 32236 H E 8 REEVES Editor GARTH C REEVES Business Manager ADVERTISING REPRESENTATIVE Interstate United Newspapers Incorporated 545 Fifth Avenue N Y b Subscription rates One Year 400 Six Months 250 Three Months 150 SATURDAY MARCH 12 1949 it4 o a CIVIL RIGHTS CONGRESS The Civil Rights Congress labelled a communist front organization by U S Attorney General Tom Clark got a plenty of adverse publicity following an interracial meet ing held at the HungarianAmerican Cultural Club last Friday Some of the organizations whose names were publicized as sponsors have declared that the names of their organizations were used without their consent One of the speakers told the press that he was trick ed into being featured speaker for the occasion A F L representative Gerald Green who addressed the meeting is reported as saying I wish there was some way of taking it all back The Rev Edward"
